# Build context for the site-builder (deploy/compose/Dockerfile.site). BuildKit prefers this
# over the root .dockerignore when the build is `-f deploy/compose/Dockerfile.site`. Unlike the
# server image (app/ only), the site build needs the website source, the card-page generator, and
# the wasm web crate — but NOT build output, VCS, node tooling, or nested worktrees.
#
# Strategy: ignore everything, then allow back exactly what build-site.sh reads.
*

# The static website source and the card-catalog page generator.
!site
!tools

# The Rust workspace — needed to build the wasm play client (trunk compiles recollect-web, which
# depends on -core/-bot/-protocol) and to read the generated catalog.json.
!app
!Cargo.toml

# The shared build script the image invokes.
!deploy/compose/build-site.sh

# Re-exclude heavy / irrelevant paths even under the allowed dirs above.
app/target
**/node_modules
**/.git
.claude
**/dist
